The paper deals with property testing of Boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves combinatorial arguments and the study of sets of variables, which are common themes in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper introduces a new measure of influence, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper uses a sample extractor and testing-by-implicit-learning approach, which are techniques commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG).
